functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

msg.content: What is the highest elevation (in feet) of the 5 largest states (by land mass) in the U.S.?
What is the highest elevation (in feet) of the 5 largest states (by land mass) in the U.S.?

The five largest states in the U.S. by land mass are:
1. Alaska - 20,310 feet
2. Texas - 8,750 feet
3. California - 14,505 feet
4. Montana - 12,799 feet
5. New Mexico - 13,167 feet

Here are the highest elevations of these states in feet:
- Alaska - Denali, 20,310 feet
- Texas - Guadalupe Peak, 8,750 feet
- California - Mount Whitney, 14,505 feet
- Montana - Granite Peak, 12,799 feet
- New Mexico - Wheeler Peak, 13,167 feet
